parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unpredictable Acceleration and Transmission Shifting Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unpredictable acceleration and transmission shifting issues can cause sudden and unexpected changes in vehicle speed, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or pauses when accelerating from a stop
accelerates suddenly
shifts unpredictably
feels like it's starting off in third gear
has inconsistent acceleration when making right-hand turns
and has difficulty shifting into drive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to fail to respond normally to the accelerator, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to fail to respond normally to the accelerator, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to shift into drive
the transmission shifts unpredictably
and the vehicle has difficulty accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective tires can lead to tire failure, which can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Bubbles on the sidewall of the tire
tire failure
sudden loss of air pressure
uneven tire wear
vibration while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose vital information about the vehicle's operation, including fuel level, temperature, and speed, which can lead to accidents or other safety issues.
symptoms: Dead pixels on the instrument cluster
inability to read fuel level
temperature
or speed
faulty or malfunctioning gauges
incomplete or inaccurate information displayed on the cluster.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle is able to restart after stalling
the engine makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty oil pressure sensor can cause the oil light to illuminate even when the oil volume is full, leading to unnecessary engine repairs and potentially causing engine damage.
symptoms: The oil light comes on despite the oil volume being full
the engine makes unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the driver is unable to stop the vehicle or react quickly enough.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal gets stuck
the vehicle accelerates rapidly without driver input
the engine RPM remains at idle for 1-3 seconds before suddenly increasing
the vehicle jumps forward or accelerates hard
and the brake pedal may not respond.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed throttle response can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially when merging into traffic or navigating busy intersections.
symptoms: The engine RPM remains at idle for 1-3 seconds before increasing
the vehicle hesitates or lags before accelerating
the vehicle jumps forward or accelerates hard after a delay.
